         <OBJECT_CONTRACT ITEM="1">
            <TITLE>
               <P>Invitation to a market dialogue 'swimming pool chemicals, water purification equipment and service of purification plants'.</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>2018/961</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="24962000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SUPPLIES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Drammen municipality will announce a competition in the near future for the procurement of swimming pool chemicals, water purification equipment and the services of purification plants (framework agreement).</P>
               <P>A decision has been made to merge Drammen, Svelvik and Nedre Eiker municipalities in 2020. Nedre Eiker has, thus, decided to be part of this procurement. The framework agreement shall, therefore, cover the need of both Drammensbadet (Drammen) and Eknes swimming pool (Nedre Eiker).</P>
               <P>The value of the procurement is estimated to be approx. NOK 6,000,000 (over four years).</P>
               <P>The aim of this prior information notice is to prevent wrong or inappropriate requirements, which put unnecessary limitations on the competition. In addition, we would like to know about any new products or systems in the market.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="43324100"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="NO032"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The aim of the procurement is to ensure that the water quality in the swimming pools is always good. The procurement shall promote a health-friendly environment for the users of Drammensbadet and Eknes swimming pool. In order to achieve this, we would like to procure chemicals and equipment that is environmentally friendly, efficient and time-saving.</P>
                  <P>We would like feedback on the following:</P>
                  <P>1) 'Requirements' (see the separate tab in Mercell):</P>
                  <P>(a) Are the requirements suitable for achieving the aim of the procurement?</P>
                  <P>(b) Are there requirements that are unnecessary that make it more costly?</P>
                  <P>(c) Are there other requirements that ought to be set?</P>
                  <P>2. Attached document 'Products':</P>
                  <P>These are the products that Drammensbadet and Eknes swimming pool currently have. We know what we currently have, but not what we potentially could have. We do not want to set requirements that restrict the competition.</P>
                  <P>(a) Chemicals Example:</P>
                  <P>()Sodium hypochlorite (liquid chlorine): We currently have 15 % strength. The question is whether we shall set the requirement at 15 %, 10-20 % (if it meets the need) or only set, for example, a requirement that the offered liquid chlorine must be 'suitable for use in a swimming pool'.</P>
                  <P>(b) The problem potentially applies to all the chemicals in the product list,</P>
                  <P>(c) Equipment, parts, etc.</P>
                  <P>We would like input regarding the product statements, so as, amongst other things, to prevent one tenderer being given preferential treatment. This particularly applies to products for the existing installations/machines, (e.g. Bermuda-MSR).</P>
                  <P>(d) Service: Is a site inspection required in order to give a fixed price for service?</P>
                  <P>(e) Other.</P>
                  <P>Other input that can promote competition and/or give better systems/products in order to achieve the aim of the procurement.</P>
                  <P>(a) We would also like feedback from tenderers who believe that everything looks ok.</P>
                  <P>The way forward.</P>
                  <P>Feedback or input can be given in two ways. Either through written feedback in the communication module in Mercell, or through a dialogue in one-to-one meetings. Tenderers who prefer one-to-one meetings are asked to register their interest through the communication module in Mercell.</P>
                  <P>The deadline for giving written feedback is Friday 9 February 2018, 16.00.</P>
                  <P>The deadline for registering your interest in one-to-one meetings is Friday 9.2.2018, 16.00.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
